commitResults.messageTitle: Implement logic components for addtask command
commitResults.messageBody:
Two main parts for this commit; AddTaskCommandParser implements parser
logic for understanding addtask command, and AddTaskCommand implements
the logical execution that makes changes to the model.

Example syntax for command is:
"addtask l\the label describing the task d\August 20 2021

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bugs, implement basic tests for AddTaskCommand and AddTaskCommandParser
commitResults.messageBody:
Some very basic tests for AddTaskCommand and AddTaskCommandParser
have been written, and bugs encountered while implementing the tests
have been remedied.

Right now, addtask accepts any input as long as both the label and
date are nonempty strings after trimming spaces. Both the label and
date fields are compulsory

Added Date and Label classes for Task fields, in the style of
existing code for Person class. Includes other necessary updates to
codebase and testcases.
